<paragraph id="6D0836D113165C48FF2DFC52C989FBBC" blockId="18.[166,1225,847,1034]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">
Bionomics. This rarely collected European species (L. 
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013165C48FC9EFC4DC955FC5F" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[872,1088,975,1002]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp, Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
) is also rare in 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113165C48FF33FC72CC3DFBBC" box="[197,296,1007,1033]" name="Ukraine" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. Single adults are usually collected from early May to the middle of August.
</paragraph>
